<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1059,1343,1453]" pageId="51" pageNumber="1010">
D i a g n o s i s: The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1844" box="[470,567,1343,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pelonium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="1010" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[470,567,1343,1364]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="1010">Pelonium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
SPINOLA was revised in 2018 (
<bibRefCitation author="OPITZ W" box="[908,1047,1343,1365]" pageId="51" pageNumber="1010" pagination="337 - 527" refId="ref53813" refString="OPITZ W. (2018 b): Classification, natural history, and evolution of the Subfamily Peloniinae OPITZ (Coleoptera: Cleroidea: Cleridae). Part X. Taxonomic revision of the New World genus Pelonium SPINOLA. - Entomofauna 39 (2): 337 - 527." type="journal article" year="2018">OPITZ 2018b</bibRefCitation>
). This work included a key to species groups and species. The available specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,335,1402,1424]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pelonium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="1010" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tayrona">
<emphasis box="[151,335,1402,1424]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="1010">Pelonium tayrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
keys out to 
<emphasis box="[462,638,1402,1424]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="1010">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1844" box="[462,559,1402,1423]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pelonium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="1010" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pelonium</taxonomicName>
circum
</emphasis>
OPITZ, from which it differs by showing more pronounced pronotal lateral tubercles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1058,1468,1579]" lastBlockId="52.[151,1059,211,409]" lastPageId="52" lastPageNumber="1011" pageId="51" pageNumber="1010">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 12.0 mm; width 4.0 mm. Form: As in 
<figureCitation box="[962,1052,1468,1491]" captionStart="Figs 334-337" captionStartId="111.[151,191,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[153,1058,199,1497]" captionTargetId="figure@111.[152,1058,199,1497]" captionTargetPageId="111" captionText="Figs 334-337: Habitus; (334) Pelonium implacide; (335) P. tayrona; (336) P. erudiatum; (337) Pujoliclerus abditus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746828" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746828/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="1010">Fig. 335</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium castaneous; antenna bicolorous, scape testaceous, remainder dark brown; pronotum mostly testaceous, disc with 2 large brown maculae; pterothorax dark brown; elytra light brown; legs bicolorous, femora and tibiae light brown, tarsi dark brown; abdomen light brown. Head: Cranium coarsely punctate; antenna (
<figureCitation box="[873,954,211,233]" captionStart="Figs 43-60" captionStartId="72.[151,191,1361,1383]" captionTargetBox="[157,1053,222,1351]" captionTargetId="figure@72.[152,1057,206,1351]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="Figs 43-60: Antennae; (43) Ordinis taxis; (44) Pelonium tayrona; (45) Neorthopleura turnbowi, male; (46) N. turnbowi, female; (47) Megaphloeus imparilus; (48) Plocamocera catalexis; (48 a) Cregya entrerios; (49) Ridica merida. (50) Kataspinula puebla. (51) Cregya tobagoensis; (52) Topainca patchacutii; (53) Eurycaulis anaxeis; (54) Amboakis expandosa. (55) Ridica achira. (56) Ampleris cacuminis; (57) Sicamus suprus; (58) Sirpa latiflava; (59) Alarius careoritus; (60) Cregya petalosa." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746750" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746750/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="1011">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
) capitate, funicular antennomeres shorter towards capitulum, capitular antennomeres 9 and 10 with short collateral branch, antennomere 11 oblong/subtruncate; eyes large, coarsely facetted, eye wider than frons (EW/FW 35/15). Thorax: Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[795,883,299,321]" captionStart="Figs 118-133" captionStartId="76.[151,191,1373,1395]" captionTargetBox="[152,1050,202,1340]" captionTargetId="figure@76.[152,1056,202,1357]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="Figs 118-133: Pronota; (118) Pujoliclerus abditus; (119) Nelsopelonium aspikelum; (120) Parapelonides naranjo; (121) Pujoliclerus lasiosus; (122) Neorthopleura rubra; (123) Pujoliclerus ariquemes; (124) Ichnea cerinis; (125) Ampleris amazon; (126) Pujoliclerus abditus; (127) P. dexsus; (128) Sirpa acara; (129) Madoniella aspera; (130) Pelonium tayrona; (131) Megatrachys irrasis; (132) Ordinis taxis; (133) Pujoliclerus cnecostus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746758" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746758/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="1011">Fig. 130</figureCitation>
) oblong (PW/PL 78/85), disc coarsely punctate, lateral tubercles well developed; elytra sculptured with small asetiferous punctures that diminish near elytral middle (EL/EW 245/65). Abdomen: Pygidium scutiform; aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation box="[633,724,387,409]" captionStart="Figs 237-242" captionStartId="89.[151,191,1264,1286]" captionTargetBox="[153,1061,198,1249]" captionTargetId="figure@89.[153,1061,198,1249]" captionTargetPageId="89" captionText="Figs 237-242: Aedeagi; (237) Cregya arima; (238) C. biguttula; (239) C. vicosa; (240) Eurycaulis anaxeis; (241) Pelonium tayrona; (242) P. implacide." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746784" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746784/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="1011">Fig. 241.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
